<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="1743" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[212,1172,420,580]" box="[212,344,420,444]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743">
<heading box="[212,344,420,444]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,344,420,444]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[212,1172,420,580]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743">
Native to Europe; introduced to 
<collectingCountry box="[610,718,459,483]" name="Australia" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743">Australia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[735,895,459,483]" name="New Zealand" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, and North and South America (
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas AK &amp; Mc Donnell &amp; RJ &amp; Paine TD &amp; Harwood JD" box="[327,556,491,515]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743" refId="ref13993" refString="Thomas AK, Mc Donnell RJ, Paine TD, Harwood JD. 2010. A field guide to the slugs of Kentucky. Lexington (Kentucky): University of Kentucky College of Agriculture- Agriculture Experiment Station Publication SR- 103." type="journal volume" year="2010">Thomas et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[620,679,491,515]" name="Chile" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743">Chile</collectingCountry>
this species has been cited from Valdivia (
<geoCoordinate box="[219,314,523,547]" degrees="39" direction="south" minutes="48" orientation="latitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743" precision="925" value="-39.8">
39°48 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[284,290,523,547]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743">ʹ</emphasis>
S
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[327,432,523,547]" degrees="73" direction="west" minutes="14" orientation="longitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743" precision="925" value="-73.23333">
73°14 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[391,397,523,547]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743">ʹ</emphasis>
W
</geoCoordinate>
) to northern 
<collectingCountry box="[584,644,523,547]" name="Chile" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743">Chile</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Landler L &amp; Nunez JJ" box="[659,941,523,547]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743" pagination="263 - 265" refId="ref11713" refString="Landler L, Nunez JJ. 2012. European invaders in South America: terrestrial snails and slugs in southern Chile. J Conchol. 41: 263 - 265." type="journal article" year="2012">Landler and Nuñez 2012</bibRefCitation>
). The first record of this species for 
<collectingCountry box="[388,448,555,579]" name="Chile" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743">Chile</collectingCountry>
was by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stuardo JR &amp; Vega R" box="[544,832,555,580]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743" pagination="125 - 146" refId="ref13768" refString="Stuardo JR, Vega R. 1985. Synopsis of the land Mollusca of Chile, with remarks on distribution. Stud Neotrop Fauna E. 20: 125 - 146." type="journal article" year="1985">Stuardo and Vega (1985)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[212,821,645,708]" box="[212,682,645,669]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743">
<heading box="[212,682,645,669]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,682,645,669]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743">Possible mechanism of introduction/Status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[212,821,645,708]" box="[212,821,684,708]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1743">
